images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Any quick fix to this problem</span><hr size=1> Several ways to do this...(long again..heh)<br>
<br>
The way I usually do it (requires a healer that's watchin out for ya...all hail Taansey, my hero!), is hit Escape, run up to the clump of critters, and do an AE stun.  If everyone is /assist'ing, the ones not being engaged will turn and pound on you.  The first one that hits you will pop up in your target box, and you can mez knowing that he's not the one your group is beating on.  <br>
<br>
This is only really feasible with 1 or 2 adds though, as you don't want TOO much beating on you.  The old-timers in the guild like to crack on my "tanking" skills, but seriously, of all the classes, enchanters are probably the best equipped to get something off of themselves, so you'll be ok.  Cross your fingers, toss off the stun, and go to town!  (NOTE:  ALWAYS have 2 stuns memmed when dungeon-hopping...that way when the adds turn to pound on you, you can toss off another stun without waiting for the 6 second recast time)<br>
<br>
Another (less painful) way is simply to use external views.  If your video card can handle the spam (mine usually can't...sigh), the overhead views are awesome.  Not only can you usually distinguish critters in a clump like that, but if you can't it's very easy to swivel the camera and pick them off without having to move yourself.<br>
<br>
Also, it might help to tell your groupies that you're having problems targetting on big pulls.  Make a hotkey that you can toss off every time you mez something, and ask your main assist to take 2 steps back every time he sees it.  Kinda' goofy, but it works.  :-)  Just let the tank know that he can jump back in after a few secs if the critter doesn't follow him.<br>
<br>
Finally, if the pulls are pretty small but clumped close together, don't try to single one out to Mez, just use Mesmerization.  A lot of 'chanters don't like the AE Mezzes, and I didn't use to, but I've kinda' rediscovered them lately.  The level 16 one only holds for 24 seconds, but it's pretty cheap to cast.  Also, don't worry if you knock yourself out, keep hitting the AE mez hotkey, you'll always wake up a few seconds before the critters do, and can recast in time.  If something resists, odds are it'll come for you, and you don't have the clump problem anymore.  :-)  Just get it out fast before the others wake up and do the same.<br>
<br>
Hope all this helps, I love talkin shop.  ;-)<br>
<br>
Tey<br>
